dcterms:description: The Tadpole dataset is used for Alzheimer's disease prediction, containing 564 patients classified into three categories (Normal, Mild Cognitive Impairment, Alzheimer's). It includes various multi-modal features such as cognitive tests, MRI ROIs, PET imaging, DTI ROI, demographics, and others.
dcterms:title: Tadpole

dcterms:description: The UK Biobank dataset consists of 14,503 patients with 440 features extracted from MRI and fMRI images, used for gender and age prediction tasks.
dcterms:title: UK Biobank
